<TR><!--Modified 6:46:46-->
<TD><FONT CLASS="newsHead"><A NAME="CanInameMyPetPlease"><B><U>Can I name My Pet, Please!</U></B></A></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD><FONT CLASS="newsFont">
<!--B-->
This was a question asked by some, that Gordon speaks to:
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<I>
Question:ust as a minor touch to the pet classes, could you implement a
                     command that lets you change the name of the pet? Might be kinda fun to do
<br><br>
Answers:We couldn't allow people to choose the name of their own pet, as it would increase the number
                     of naming issues by an order of magnitude. Also, changing the name of a pet after summoning
                     isn't an option, due to the way that the zone keeps track of NPCs. The only possible change
                     that we could even look into would be for people to choose an NPC name from a list of
                     acceptable names, causing future pets to be named in that fashion, however something like
                     this isn't likely to be prioritized anytime soon.
</I>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<BR>
-Dragons - <FONT SIZE="-2">6:46 AM MST</FONT><BR><BR>
<!--E-->
<CENTER><A HREF="#Top">Top</A></CENTER>
</FONT>
<BR>
</TD>
</TR><!--End Item-->
<TR><!--Modified 6:42:18-->
<TD><FONT CLASS="newsHead"><A NAME="HeyWhatHappenedToTheOnlineStore"><B><U>Hey What Happened To The Online Store!</U></B></A></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD><FONT CLASS="newsFont">
<!--B-->
Its been gone for some time, but what happened to it? Brad himself speaks on that:
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<I>
Hello all,
<br><br>
                     First, sorry about the void of information regarding the online store -- we've not only been working
                     on a total revamp of the store internally, but also have been working with distributors.
<br><br>
                     It's looking good at this point, and internally we've set a target date of September 1 for the
                     re-launch. The date isn't set in stone and we'll keep you up to date as we get closer and closer. But
                     at least there is light at the end of the tunnel.
<br><br>
                     We appreciate your patience in this matter,
</I>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<BR>
-Dragons - <FONT SIZE="-2">6:42 AM MST</FONT><BR><BR>
<!--E-->
<CENTER><A HREF="#Top">Top</A></CENTER>
</FONT>
<BR>
</TD>
</TR><!--End Item-->
<TR><!--Modified 6:41:02-->
<TD><FONT CLASS="newsHead"><A NAME="FeedbackOnTheUserInterface"><B><U>Feedback On The User Interface</U></B></A></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD><FONT CLASS="newsFont">
<!--B-->
Over at the official <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/003400.html">GamePlay</a> board Roy (A senior Programmer) has started a thread to ask for your views on the User Interface.  Here is what he says:
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<I>
My name is Roy, and I am a Senior Programmer on the EQ Live team.
                     My main focus for now is the client program including the User
                     Interface.
<br><br>
                     Some of the first things I've done are now live and I've seen the many
                     reactions to them. I've been reading the boards and even implemented
                     some of the suggestions already (they will go onto test tonight or
                     tomorrow).
<br><br>
                     Be aware that while I am reading the boards, I can not respond to
                     everything. I will read what I can, and respond when I can. If I were to
                     spend the time needed to reply to everything, then I would not have
                     any time to code the changes and fixes needed. My boss would not be
                     too happy with me, if that were the case...
<br><br>
                     Hopefully, we can work together to make the UI as good as it can be.

</I>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<BR>
-Dragons - <FONT SIZE="-2">6:41 AM MST</FONT><BR><BR>
<!--E-->
<CENTER><A HREF="#Top">Top</A></CENTER>
</FONT>
<BR>
</TD>
</TR><!--End Item-->
<TR><!--Modified 6:36:19-->
<TD><FONT CLASS="newsHead"><A NAME="MoRishiring"><B><U>MoR is hiring!</U></B></A></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD><FONT CLASS="newsFont">
<!--B-->
<b>MoR is hiring!</b>
<br>
<p>What is MoR? It stands for <b><i>Mirrors of Reality</b></i>, which will be one of our up and coming xroads network sites!.
The main focus of the site will be on fantasy literature and artwork.  If you've ever wanted to express your views on the fantasy
novel you just read, or felt the urge to shout your concepts about the fantasy genre from the mountain tops, you might want to
think about signing up.  We're looking for people to write reviews, editorials, help out with interviews and a whole bunch of other
tasks.
<p>What kind of applicants are we looking for?
<ul>
<li>General knowledge of the fantasy realm genre, including having read a sizable chunk of fantasy books from multiple
authors.</li>
<li>Some writing ability, previous work would be a plus. Keep in mind this isn't neccesarily
an avenue where roleplaying is needed in the writing, but previous work with roleplaying content would be looked at.</li>
<li>The ability to put in some writing time at a weekly level[doesn't need to be daily, but that would be a plus], not on a strict
schedule, but with an eventual deadline.</li>
<li>No RPG, MMORPG, or fantasy based gaming experience needed!</li></ul>
<p>Please fill out an application <a href="http://www.xrgaming.com/jobapp.php3" target="_blank">here</a> if you are interested.
For more information please email <a href="mailto:jester@xrgaming.net">Jester</a>.
<BR><BR>
-Dragons - <FONT SIZE="-2">6:36 AM MST</FONT><BR><BR>
<!--E-->
<CENTER><A HREF="#Top">Top</A></CENTER>
</FONT>
<BR>
